div.p:
In the year 761, Oengus,Cf. supra, sub 750. king of the Picts, died;
who, from the beginning to the end of his reign, continued
to be a blood-stained and tyrannical butcher;
OswinAn aetheling killed by Moll, king of Northumbria, at a place
called Edwin's Cliff (Sax. Chron.). was also slain.
